title: More than 100,000 people march in Paris to protest antisemitism
description:
More than 100,000 protesters took to the streets of Paris to denounce an increase in antisemitism amid the Israel-Hamas war. Notable participants included Prime Minister Elisabeth Borne, former presidents Nicolas Sarkozy and Francois Hollande, as well as
far-right leader Marine Le Pen.

title: In very rare move, Pope dismisses conservative U.S. bishop
description: Pope Francis has dismissed Bishop Joseph E. Strickland of Texas, a vocal critic of his who opposed attempts to make the church more welcoming to the LGBTQ community.
